subsection.def:
approved
                    (認可) means approved by the Director for the
                purposes of this Ordinance;

charge
                    (控訴) means a complaint, information, charge
                or indictment;

paragraph.content:
any Convention or Protocol specified in a notice under subsection (4)
                        to be a Convention or Protocol for the purposes of this Ordinance;
                        and

authorizing the diversion of such drug to a country other than that
                        specified in the export authorization relating to that drug as the country
                        to which it was to be exported;

subsection.def:
ecgonine
                    (芽子鹼) means laevo-ecgonine and any
                derivatives of ecgonine from which it may be recovered industrially;

export
                    (出口) means to take or cause to be taken out
                of Hong Kong or any other country, as the case may be, by land, air or water;

ship
                    (船舶) includes every description of vessel
                used in navigation or for the carriage or storage of goods on water;

paragraph.content:
authorize a registered dentist to supply a dangerous drug unless the drug
                    is administered by him, or under his direct supervision and in his presence, to
                    a person receiving treatment by him;

subparagraph.content:
in accordance with a written order signed by the sister in charge of a
                        ward, theatre or other department in the hospital, health centre or clinic;
                        or

paragraph.content:
subject to the provisions of this Ordinance, to carry on at any such
                    premises the business of retailing, dispensing and compounding any dangerous
                    drug;

section 1 of Schedule 2 to the Merchant Shipping (Collision
                        Damage Liability and Salvage) Ordinance (Cap.
                            508);

subparagraph.content:
that the document is a true copy of the records or
                                                part of the records of the Land Registry;
                                                and

subsection.def:
ship
                    (船舶) includes any vessel used in navigation
                and includes a hovercraft;

paragraph.content:
for the purpose of obtaining, whether for himself or for any other person,
                    the issue or renewal of a licence or certificate under this Ordinance, makes any
                    declaration or statement which is false in a material particular;

knowingly utters, produces or makes use of any such declaration or
                    statement or a document containing any such declaration or statement;
                    or

section.def:
Registry
                (檔案室) means the Central Registry of Drug Abuse
            referred to in section 49B;

paragraph.content:
the keeping of registers and other records by persons authorized by or
                    licensed under this Ordinance to manufacture, procure, supply or possess
                    dangerous drugs, and the furnishing of information by such persons;

remove by force any person or thing who or which obstructs any entry,
                    search, inspection, seizure, removal or detention which he is empowered by this
                    section to make;

any money or thing (other than premises, a ship exceeding 250 gross tons,
                    an aircraft or a train) which has been used in the commission of or in
                    connection with;

by replacement of the phenyl portion of the phenethyl group by any
                            heteromonocycle whether or not further substituted in the
                            heterocycle;

by replacement of the 1-methyl group by an acyl, alkyl whether or
                            not unsaturated, benzyl or phenethyl group, whether or not further
                            substituted;

by formation of an N-oxide or of a quarternary base;
                                (Amended L.N. 7 of
                                2011)

by replacement of the amino group with a 1-piperidyl, 1-pyrrolidyl
                            or 1-azepyl group, whether or not the nitrogen containing ring is
                            further substituted with one or more alkyl groups;

by substitution in the phenyl ring to any extent with amino, alkyl,
                            hydroxy, alkoxy or halide substituents, whether or not further
                            substituted in the phenyl ring to any extent;
